product - Variable in class Controller.ModifyProductController
This Product variable enables the two product controllers to communicate and transfer data of the selected product being modified.
It will be reinitialized with the selected product object to be modified.
Product - Class in Model
This is the Product class and this class handles all the product's getters and setters.
This class also handles the associated parts for all products.
Product(int, String, double, int, int, int) - Constructor for class Model.Product
The constructor method for products.
It initializes the id, name, price, stock, maximum, and minimum for each product object.
productAssociatedParts - Static variable in class Controller.AddProductController
Array list that will contain the associated parts added into the associatedPartsTable.
This list will be passed over to be added into the associatedPartsTable in the Product class and will be referenced for the instance of product being created.
productId - Static variable in class Controller.AddProductController
Variable that contains the unique ID value for each product.

It is initialized to 999 initially, because when the first product is added in the saveProduct method, productId is incremented by 1 making the first product id value 1000.
